  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/commit/95bf73f493dc8458a1d6981493275379197a4bdf\r\n* OS: linux\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.10.8\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nFor functions that perform internal calls conditionally, the cost of memory expansion for the internal call is always paid even if the internal function is not called, because the caller memory frame is placed at higher memory addresses than the callees memory frame.\r\n\r\nh/t @trocher @ptrcarta\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nFill this in if you know how to fix it.\r\n",
